    },
    {
      "id": "o33lcSmwrLtPwvQLR3hex",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1881.7116650697792,
      "y": 4891.301986922381,
      "width": 1837.4755859375,
      "height": 1665,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#a5d8ff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bES",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1469938890,
      "version": 1589,
      "versionNonce": 1393084042,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1769795731854,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. Create New Repo in Github -> Django Projects\n2. Clone this repo in some folder -> Like Developer\n3. Open Developer Folder in VS code \n4. Go Inside Developer Folder in terminal  then Django Projects\n5. create project folder name inside Django Project like project_middleware\n6 Go inside project_middleware create Virtual Environment -> python3 -m virtualenv venv\n7 Activate this virtualenv -> source venv/bin/activate\n8 install django -> pip install django\n9 create project -> django-admin startproject djmiddleware . -> it will create djmiddleware project inside \n    project_middleware folder, it will not create extra folder named djmiddleware\n10 create premade schema using python manage.py migrate\n11 create apps like middleware using -> python manage.py startapp middleware\n12 add this app is settings.py in INSTALLED_APPS list\n\n\n\nQ -> When db.sqlite3 created ?  -> will check in next project\nQ -> When migrations folder created?\n\n\n\n.gitignore -> __pycache__/\n                *.pyc\n                *.pyo\n                *.pyd\n                  \n                db.sqlite3\n                venv/\n                .gitignore\n\nIf we forgot to add lets say .gitignore then how we can remove that from pushed code then ignore?\n\n    rm .gitignore\n    git commit -m 'remove commit'\n    git push\n    \n",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. Create New Repo in Github -> Django Projects\n2. Clone this repo in some folder -> Like Developer\n3. Open Developer Folder in VS code \n4. Go Inside Developer Folder in terminal  then Django Projects\n5. create project folder name inside Django Project like project_middleware\n6 Go inside project_middleware create Virtual Environment -> python3 -m virtualenv venv\n7 Activate this virtualenv -> source venv/bin/activate\n8 install django -> pip install django\n9 create project -> django-admin startproject djmiddleware . -> it will create djmiddleware project inside \n    project_middleware folder, it will not create extra folder named djmiddleware\n10 create premade schema using python manage.py migrate\n11 create apps like middleware using -> python manage.py startapp middleware\n12 add this app is settings.py in INSTALLED_APPS list\n\n\n\nQ -> When db.sqlite3 created ?  -> will check in next project\nQ -> When migrations folder created?\n\n\n\n.gitignore -> __pycache__/\n                *.pyc\n                *.pyo\n                *.pyd\n                  \n                db.sqlite3\n                venv/\n                .gitignore\n\nIf we forgot to add lets say .gitignore then how we can remove that from pushed code then ignore?\n\n    rm .gitignore\n    git commit -m 'remove commit'\n    git push\n    \n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
